                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d795">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00111 A.R/1051: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-13T23:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 13, 1940—11 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>35. Your 66, May 13, 6 p.m. The text of the Uruguayan draft is being telegraphed
                        tonight<note n="61" xml:id="d795fn61">Circular telegram, May 13, 11 p.m.,
                        not printed.</note> to our missions in the 11 countries specified in your
                    telegram under reference with the request that it be placed promptly before the
                    Governments concerned and that the latter cable their reply to the President of
                    Panama without delay. It is being indicated at the same time that the Government
                    of the United States is in full agreement with the text.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
